<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 3:52PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Shelby
County through 430 PM CDT...
At 352 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Columbiana. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Columbiana, Wilsonville, Lay Lake, Shelby, Beeswax Creek Park,
Alabama 4H Center, Highway 145 and CR 46, Spring Creek, Kelley Branch
and Shelby Shores.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
